commentPostTextItems.html: The presentation is left, don't go anywhere

Man of the Match Chibhabha: I was under a bit of pressure leading up to this game and happy to spend some time in the middle. It was important for me to stay there and not lose wickets, and build some momentum. It's always very important to work through the beginning and build a solid start, I was happy with my performance. This wicket was pretty flat so it was important to hit the deck hard.

Asghar Stanikzai: Bowlers did a good job but we batted poorly again and the total was achievable because wicket was good for batting. Our batsmen played poor shots and didn't take responsibility. Our spinners bowled very well especially towards the end.

Elton Chigumbura: Guys worked hard to come back from 0-2 and credit goes to openers today to not lose a wicket in 15 overs. And credit to Chamu as well for bowling well. The way we finished our innings was not that good and we were looking to score around 260. We've started the new year on a positive note and hope to win the series now.

That's it from us then, the series is 2-2 and join us on January 6 (Wednesday) now for the decider. If you missed any of the action, here's Shashank Kishore's match report here. Until the next match, goodbye and good luck from Vishal Dikshit.

10.28pm So the series is alive even though Zimbabwe were 2-0 down and 49 for 7 in the third ODI, but they have come back and how! Today also they won the toss and put up a score that could be thought of defending even though they crumbled towards the end of their innings. But their top order got some runs. And once Madziva got the early wickets again, Jongwe kept the pressure up and Chibhabha followed his fifty with his maiden four-for to finish things off

commentTextItems.html: extra bounce surprises Hamza as he looked to defend off the back foot and took it on the glove eventually
back of length now outside off, punched into the covers
tries a yorker and it goes down leg for a wide
drives it away from the body without moving his feet and misses!
angled in towards the off stump, blocked back to the bowler again
in the block hole around off, Dawlat blocks it back
pokes and misses outside off, it was back of length and he went after it but missed
pretty wide outside off and it's steered towards point now
in the block hole around off, he blocks it to the leg side
flicked in the air off the pads and that's gone in the gap wide of long-on for two
pretty wide outside off and shaping away further, he steers it away to cover point

commentPreTextItems.html: Madziva comes back after a long break

commentTextItems.html: back of length on off and it's pushed into the covers
dances down, Cremer sends it down slower and Dawlat pushes it down gently to long on
comes down again and slogs, gets some bat on that to the leg side
googly turns into the batsman, and he's cramped for room to put it away
charges down, gets some bat and lofts it down the ground, but it falls well short of long on

the straighter one goes through everything! Pitched on length around off and that went through the gap between bat and pad, and then through the keeper for four byes. A fielder chases, puts in a dive but that only rams the ball into the ad cones at the boundary
full on the pads, it's flicked away nicely in the air and behind square on the leg side

dismissalText.commentary: Malcolm Waller c Hashmatullah Shahidi b Mirwais Ashraf 15 (18b 1x4 0x6) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: catch taken at second attempt in Cape Town and it's the same in Sharjah too - he's cut it straight to point. It was short outside off, he cut it fiercely off the back foot and Hashmatullah Shahidi tried to take it over his head with both hands, the ball popped out and took it comfortably the second time

dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha c Asghar Afghan b Rashid Khan 53 (92b 1x4 1x6) SR: 57.6

dismissalComment.html: great catch from the captain and look at that beaming smile! Chibhabha went for a slog-sweep when the ball wasn't that full, he tried to go over midwicket but Stanikzai jumped and plucked it out with one hand!

dismissalText.long: c Mohammad Nabi b Amir Hamza
dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza c Mohammad Nabi b Amir Hamza 26 (40b 3x4 0x6) SR: 65

dismissalComment.html: another one down, this time it's Masakadza caught! It was short and wide, Masakadza slammed it with hard hands through the off side and Nabi jumped at cover to catch it with both hands

dismissalText.commentary: Richmond Mutumbami c Shafiqullah b Amir Hamza 14 (20b 1x4 0x6) SR: 70

dismissalComment.html: fifth one down, all caught! Mutumbami went down on a knee to sweep that fullish delivery to the leg side, he didn't muscle that very well and Shafiqullah had to dive to his right to get his fingers under it as the ball was dipping. Well done after that misfield in the last over

dismissalText.commentary: Sikandar Raza b Dawlat Zadran 9 (12b 1x4 0x6) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: inside edge onto the stumps, Raza is gone too! There wasn't much room and the ball nipped in too from outside off, Raza stayed back and tried to steer it to third man with a horizontal bat but got a bottom edge onto the off stump

dismissalText.long: c Mohammad Nabi b Dawlat Zadran

dismissalComment.html: another good catch taken over the head! Cremer got a full delivery and wanted to clear mid-off, he lofted it alright but Nabi backpedalled a few steps and took it very well over his head with both hands
